  "prompt": "Has anyone received any call from companies, cut-off of which has been been cleared in LinkedIn Placements Test?",
  "response": "**LinkedIn Placements Test** is often used by companies to assess candidates' skills in various domains like programming, problem-solving, and aptitude. If you have cleared the cut-off for a particular company's LinkedIn Placement Test, you may indeed receive a call or email from the company or their recruitment team for further rounds of the hiring process.\n\nHere\u2019s what typically happens:\n\n1. **Clearing the Cut-Off**: If your score meets or exceeds the company's predefined cut-off, you qualify for the next stage of the hiring process.\n\n2. **Communication from the Company**: The company or their recruitment team may reach out to you via:\n   - **Email**: A formal invitation for the next round (e.g., technical interview, HR interview, etc.).\n   - **Phone Call**: A recruiter might call you to discuss the next steps or schedule an interview.\n   - **LinkedIn Message**: Some recruiters might contact you directly through LinkedIn.\n\n3. **Next Steps**: Depending on the company, the next stages could include:\n   - Technical interviews\n   - HR interviews\n   - Coding challenges\n   - Group discussions or case studies\n\nIf you haven\u2019t received any communication yet, here\u2019s what you can do:\n- **Check Your Email**: Ensure you\u2019ve checked your spam or promotions folder, as emails can sometimes land there.\n- **LinkedIn Messages**: Regularly check your LinkedIn messages and connection requests.\n- **Follow Up**: If you know the company\u2019s recruitment contact, it\u2019s okay to send a polite follow-up email or message after a reasonable waiting period (e.g., 1-2 weeks).\n\nGood luck with your placement process!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
